metadata.name: Annum #6023
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Manu #37
metadata.description:
Manu
---------------

A collector-led exploration of minimalist imperfect line work.

Outputs are generated from a combination of the minter's address, their choice from one of 50 seeds, and options to adjust how the generated surface is presented.

Palettes are named after native New Zealand birds and range from the subdued to the colorful.

There are no especially rare traits so mint what you love :)

---------------

Controls:
S - Export as png
H - Toggle high resolution

metadata.name: Our Tune #21
metadata.description:
A love song from an engine that has never heard one. Our Tune tells a four part story of two people's time together and sometimes apart. Do not expect sweetness, though it may happen.

Operation: Touch once to unmute, then let it play through or touch again to cycle.

[[[Best with headphones]]]

metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.

metadata.name: Rapport #14
metadata.description:
The concept of nexus is a powerful one. It speaks to the idea that everything is related and that each part is necessary to create the whole. Rapport is about the relationship these parts have, harmonious or discordant, to convey a sense of unity and purpose. You are invited to explore the details and interactions of each object in its surroundings, recognizing the immense value they all have in building greater things.

A few shortcuts are available in live mode:
1 : Toggle the view (fit screen / original size)
T : Toggle paper texture
S : Save current view
H : Re-render in high resolution

The piece might require high processing power depending on its features. A good desktop or laptop running chrome is recommended.

Created with p5.js and GLSL
dmarchi, 2023.

metadata.name: twofiftythousand #297
metadata.description:
twofiftythousand is about the chaos of unlimited decisions. Look for a pattern in the noise.

Press 's' to save an image while in full-screen mode.

If you want to increase the resolution of the saved image, add e.g. &size=2000 after the live/fullscreen view URL to render the canvas at that specific pixel width (default = browser sized). This will be dependent on your system specifications, but outputs of up to 8000px wide, or above, should be possible.

metadata.name: Code Page 437 // Ishihara #208
metadata.description:
In order to understand what you see before your eyes you must first open this artwork in both Firefox and any other web browser of your choice, at the same time, to experience it as intended.

A combination of ishihara palettes and cross-browser bugs are used to explore neurodiversity by forcing the viewer to take additional manual steps to see the world from a different perspective. A whole new understanding of colour blindness should unfold as you struggle through inaccessibility yourself.

The 640x400px canvas consists of 25 rows, with 80 columns per row for a total of 2000 letters, using only 16 glyphs from the Codepage 437 character set scaled to a resolution of 8x16 pixels per character.

Codepage 437 is the original IBM PC-ASCII font from August 1981, often referred to as the DOS font.

metadata.name: walkinthepark #91
metadata.description:
Mazes are almost entierly context-free. The mazes of `walkinthepark` have no entrance or exit. Not all of them are solvable. Any resemblance to reality is pure coincidence.

All features are distributed equally:
- weave - The internal pattern of sub-mazes.
- density - The density of the sub-mazes.
- color - Yep.
- aim - How big the biggest sub-maze can get.
- bars - How connected sub-mazes are.
- stroke - The randomness of lines.
- skew - How much some sub-mazes are rotated.
- grain - How many sub-mazes are rotated.

@balidani, Dec 2021

metadata.name: Multi-Biome #128
metadata.description:
Inspired by Jose Margulis's "Alpine Landscape"

Designed to be viewed as if you're walking past on the gallery wall, Multi-Biome is an interative play on perspective and scale. Each landscape is created from between 50 and 200 planes, slicing the landscape along a single axis.

Click and drag to rotate.

Press "s" in live view to save a png.

metadata.name: Plottable Letters #24
metadata.description:
Plottable Letters plays with letters, digits, and basic shapes. There is a great chance to obtain a "GM", but also many other letter combination.

More info: https://greweb.me/plots/368

The digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art: Owning this NFT confers the right to request a physical plot (A4 square, 21cm by 21cm) – this is an optional possibility as you can already enjoy the digital version.

Digital and Physical art, hybrid and decoupled:
- art published via a digital NFT on Tezos – its digital representation simulates fountain pen inks drawing on paper with animated effects.
- Token to the physical world: owning each NFT confer the power to request the related physical plot at https://greweb.me/plots/nft

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Coupé Décalé #240
metadata.description:
Coupé-Décalé is a type of popular dance music originating in Côte d'Ivoire (Ivory Coast).
The term Coupé-Décalé means cut-shifted in french.
A name that perfectly defines the process used in this generative series.

Artist: Estienne
Dec. 2021 / Jan. 2022
